  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a kazan cauldron over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes.",
    "Add the callaloo, chicken broth, flour, salt, and black pepper to the cauldron.",
    "Stir to combine and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.",
    "Remove the cauldron from the heat and stir in the butter until melted.",
    "Sprinkle the chopped parsley on top of the pilaf and serve hot.",
    "Let the pilaf rest for 5 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld together."
